The paper proposes an automated sleep staging system using deep learning, specifically a deep recurrent neural network. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of neural networks also suggests the possibility of it being categorized under neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). The paper also mentions the use of EEG signals, which could potentially fall under computer vision (cs.CV) if image processing techniques were used. Finally, the paper discusses the potential impact of the system on making expert-level sleep analysis more widely available, which could fall under human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
